{
  "texts": [
    "Let's denote the input image as X ∈ R (H×W×C) re H, W, and C, respectively, represent the height, breadth, and number of channels.",
    "Each patch has a dimension of P × P, and there are N patches in total.",
    "The input embedding can be represented the as E ∈ R (N×D) where D is the number of dimen- sions of the embeddings.",
    "The input embeddings include positional information to capture the relative and absolute positions of the patches.",
    "The positional encoding matrix P ∈ R (N×D) added to the input embeddings E element by element."
  ]
}